# ── Encryption model ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Committed:   media.json.age, media-age/<uuid>.age, key.age (passphrase-wrapped
#              private key), .age-recipient (public key, not secret).
# Never commit: the plaintext key, the plaintext manifest, or decrypted media.
#
# NOTE: gitignore has NO inline comments — anything after a pattern on the same
# line becomes part of the pattern. Keep every comment on its own line.

# the decrypted private identity — the secret that unlocks everything
key.txt
*.identity
# the decrypted manifest
media.json
# decrypted working copies of all media
media/

# ── Raw media (belt and braces) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# media/ is already ignored, but ignore stray plaintext media anywhere too, so a
# file dropped at the repo root can never be committed unencrypted. A name
# ending in .age does not match these, so the encrypted copies still commit.
*.jpg
*.jpeg
*.png
*.gif
*.webp
*.bmp
*.tif
*.tiff
*.heic
*.heif
*.avif
*.mov
*.mp4
*.m4v
*.webm
*.avi
*.mkv
*.mpg
*.mpeg
*.wmv
*.flv

# ── Example library (deliberately public, unencrypted samples) ───────────────
# Re-include everything under examples/ so the demo media commits despite the
# media-extension rules above. These are generated test patterns — no PII.
!examples/
!examples/**

# ── Secrets / local-only ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.catbox-userhash

# ── macOS / editor cruft ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~
node_modules/
